class Solution {
public:
    bool makeStringsEqual(string s, string target) {
        int n = s.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (s[i] != target[i]) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the characters of both strings and checks if they are equal. If any characters are not equal, it immediately returns false. Otherwise, it returns true, indicating that the strings are equal after applying the operations. The time complexity is O(n) because the algorithm iterates through the strings once. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm uses a constant amount of space. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few operations and does not consume significant energy.

